I&#x27;m not going to attempt to speak for java, but at least in C#, it supports virtual static methods in interfaces, including generics.<p>So, as I stated, you would use the interface keyword.<p><pre><code>  public interface IFromString&lt;T&gt;
  {
      static abstract T FromString(string value);
  }

  public struct MyHasFromString : IFromString&lt;MyHasFromString&gt;
  {
      public string Text = &quot;&quot;;

      public MyHasFromString(string value) 
      {
          Text = value;
      }

      public static MyHasFromString FromString(string value)
          =&gt; return new MyHasFromString(value);

      public override string ToString() =&gt; Text;
  }</code></pre>
